title: 820-02020 5V 0.04A and clicking sound
message:
Board got liquid damage around JT400, Q5240, CC337.

Found short on PP5V_S2, replaced UP700 and short gone.
Got 5V and 0.04A from charger and I can hear clicking sound on the board - transistor?
Cant locate precise the location of that sound.
Any idea?

title: 820-02020 5V 0.04A and clicking sound
message:
Check diode mode to ground on all secondary power rails.
Compare with good board, or reference table:
[URL unfurl="true"]https://openboarddata.org/?a=showboardsolutions&bpath=laptops/apple/820-02020[/URL]

title: 820-02020 5V 0.04A and clicking sound
message:
PP1V06_S2SW_DRAM - 0.001 in diode mode and 2.5 Ohm to ground

Removed J7740/1 and R770A to check if U7700 is shorted and it is not shorted.
Because PP1V06_S2SW_DRAM going to the RAM any safe suggestion how to find what is shorted?

title: 820-02020 5V 0.04A and clicking sound
message: Inject 1-1.2V there and use an IR cam.

title: 820-02020 5V 0.04A and clicking sound
message: They only components which are getting a little bit warmer are both RAM chips.
